programme.title: The Crimson Palm

programme.title: Heaven Sword & Dragon Sabre
programme.desc: In the Yuan Dynasty, martial artists everywhere battle for the Heaven Sword and the Dragon Sabre. When these two powerful weapons combine, can a secret be revealed to help one become the king of the martial arts world.

programme.title: The Comedy Of Mismatches
programme.desc: Two pairs of lovers got mismatched accidentally. The man disguises as a woman for his sister's wedding ceremony, while his lover disguises as a man to marry another woman.

programme.title: Cat Vs Rat
programme.desc: When young martial artist 'The Rat' unwittingly rescues the emperor from a gang of thieves, it sets in motion a chain of events that see him compete for his life against 'The Cat'.

programme.title: The Dream Of The Red Chamber
programme.desc: The fruitless love between Bao Yu and Dai Yu. The marriage of this beloved couple seems next to impossible, as the ruthless mother of Bao Yu deliberately arranges the marriage of his son with another lady.

programme.title: Godfather Of Canton
programme.desc: A commissioner is arrested by envoy Cheng for corruption with an unintentional helped of Lin. Working for Cheng, Lin soon learns how to get dockside bribes spin-off from Chang.

programme.title: Puppy Love
programme.desc: This is a story of adolescent playfulness and innocence lost. Two best friends grow up together, but rivalry intervenes when they discover boys!

programme.title: Buddha's Palm
programme.desc: Word gets out that blind Ku (Alex Man Chi-leung) has the secret of the Buddha's Palm and he is besieged by everything from terrifying giant birds to gangs of martial arts warriors.

programme.title: The Twin Bracelets
programme.desc: When two childhood friends in a remote community vow to live as sisters forever, the stage is set for a drama of tragic proportions when, years later, one leaves to get married.

programme.title: Killer Darts
programme.desc: Rampaging bandits are raping and pillaging all over peaceful Chinese villages until the grieving dart master Liu Wen Lung sets out with his student, son, and servant to avenge his murdered wife and set things right.

programme.title: Two Con Men
programme.desc: A wonderfully twisted, pseudo-romantic comedy starring Liang Tien and Chang Ying in an age-old competition between rookie con artist versus the ultimate, experienced flimflam man.

programme.title: The Devil's Mirror
programme.desc: Sun Chung hit the ground running with this action-filled tale of a 'Devil Girl' who is setting one clan against another to get her hands on two amazing mirrors with supernatural powers.

programme.title: The Purple Shell
programme.desc: Hui Pui-ching is often ill-treated by her husband Fan Pak-nan, a cruel and uncouth man. At a party, Pui-ching meets rich and erudite businessman, Ha Mon-hin and they are mutually attracted.

programme.title: Return Of The Crazy Bumpkins
programme.desc: Sequel to the John Lo Mar/Chang Yang original finds immigrant Yeh Feng leaving jail to live with crooked uncle Wang Sha, but his girlfriend Ai Ti has married an abusive husband.

programme.title: My Rebellious Son

programme.title: The Scandalous Warlord
programme.desc: General Feng occupies the city of Shandong, and soldiers and civilians alike welcome him without knowing his tyrannical and lustful nature.

programme.title: Pursuit Of Vengeance
programme.desc: Kung Fu legend Ti Lung stars in the action movie as Fu Xue Hong, embarking on a epic journey of revenge for his father.

programme.title: The Grand Substitution

programme.title: The Avenging Eagle
programme.desc: One of the most beloved martial arts dramas of all-time chronicles the Thirteen Eagles Assassination Sect of the Iron Boat clan and the formidable warriors united by tragedy.

programme.title: The Three Smiles
programme.desc: A talented scholar, Bo Hu, is attracted by the pretty maid, Qiu Xiang. In order to get close to her and win her love, he disguises as a servant to work in the same household.

programme.title: Heroes Of Sung
programme.desc: Starring Shih Szu, one of the original action heroines of HK cinema, here she teams up with Lo Lieh to find and protect the royal seals of the Sung Dynasty in this kung-fu classic.

programme.title: Apartment For Ladies

programme.title: Village Of Tigers

programme.title: The Empress Dowager

programme.title: Iron Bodyguard

programme.title: Crazy Shaolin Disciples
